{"questionId":"29618869","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>Q</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p>Find</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-part\" data-part=\"2\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p></div></div>","markschemeHtml":"<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"0\"><p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to cancel factors and substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to expand denominator, differentiate numerator and denominator twice and substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>18</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-ms-part\" data-part=\"1\"><p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to consider coefficients of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math> or divide all terms by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>terms</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>which</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>tend</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>to</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>terms</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>which</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>tend</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>to</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to cancel factors and consider coefficients of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> or divide all terms by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to expand denominator, differentiate numerator and denominator three times</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>18</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfenced><mfrac><mn>18</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If the <em><strong>M1</strong></em> has not been awarded in part (i) it can be awarded in part (ii).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p></div>","meta":{"questionId":"29618869","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.11f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find limx→-1fx; limx→∞fx.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.13—Limits and L’Hopitals"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}